Ok, final message of the day.  I went ahead and compiled ATLAS 3.9.76
(http://sourceforge.net/projects/math-atlas/files/Developer%20%28unstable%29/)
from scratch using the following configure script:

cd /pathto/ATLAS
mkdir my_build_dir
cd my_build_dir
../configure --prefix=/pathto/atlas --dylibs
make
make install

Using the *libtatlas.so* (the threaded version -- note that ATLAS will
also install *libsatlas.so*, but this is a serial execution version
and serves no purpose), I am now getting parallel BLAS and no problems
using Rmpi in an interactive mode (and with StatET).  Both are
executing properly across all the cores.  I tried ATLAS a number of
years ago on a different system and never got it working, but it
appears to be working now!

--j

