Wanted to follow up on this using OpenBLAS 0.1.1 with the affinity
flag commented out -- I did try:
require(parallel)
cl <- makeCluster(12,type="MPI")
# R spawns are running on a single core
mcaffinity(1:12)
# No change, the R spawns are still running on a single core.

In terms of your comment about the Intel MKL -- is it possible to run
this as a shared dynamic library?  If so, I was never able to figure
out what specific file to link against with our local install of Intel
MKL (i.e. what is the swap-in for libRblas.so?).

--j


